First, need to get some libraries:

library(ggplot2)
library(purrr)

Then, make a function just for plotting iris data.

plot_iris <- function(y_var){
    ggplot(iris,
           aes_string(x = "Species", 
               y = y_var, 
               colour = "Species")) +
        geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, notch = TRUE) +
        geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(w = 0.5), size = 3, alpha = I(1/2)) +
        scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
        labs(title = y_var) +
        theme_minimal(base_size = 10)
}

Now, run (i.e. purrr::map) each of the columns into plot_iris(). This is effectively like a for loop.

iris_plots <- map(colnames(iris)[1:4], ~ plot_iris(y_var = .x))

Finally, here is what you get as you step through iris_plots.

iris_plots[[1]]

iris_plots[[2]]

iris_plots[[3]]

iris_plots[[4]]
